Register usage

A	main accumulator
B	scratch for compares etc

YA	Return for 32bit values, Y is the top half
A	Return for 16bit or 8bit values

X	Stack linkage, working register (not saved)
Y	Free
Z	Frame pointer

Types

char	8bit default unsigned, lower register half

int	16bit. Occupies one register

pointer	16bit. Occupies one register

long:	32bit. Occupies a pair of registers

float:	32bit. Occupies a pair of registers.

All objects in memory are big endian.

Call Interface

Stack based

Stack

Downwards off S (defined by hardware)

Alignment

Byte


